Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on mobile edge computing, which is a networking and architecture concept. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a resource management algorithm for edge servers, which is a distributed computing problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper addresses the challenge of delivering a high quality of service in renewable-powered mobile edge computing systems, which involves control and optimization of system performance. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based algorithm for resource management, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based algorithm for resource management, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence.
